	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That's what I meant by &quot;make the first few sectors of the ROM self-flashable, with a library that copies files in and out of a log-structured file system.&quot; But if we go that route, the library would have to be extra careful not to brick the game, or we'd need logic in the mapper CPLD to allow write enables to go through to the flash chip only in low-numbered outer banks. (Anyone remember bridging SL1 when installing FlashMe custom firmware on a DS?)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


